28/03/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Turkish Chief of Staff General Hilmi Ozkok voiced strong support Monday (27 March) for Macedonia's NATO membership bid, during a visit to Skopje. Ozkok said Macedonia deserves an invitation to join the Pact, given the country's progress in reforms, which he says serve as a positive example for the region. (Macedonian Government Web site - 28/03/06; Makfax - 27/03/06)
